   Introduction
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Croins is an Asteroids-clone game, but more coloured and various.


   System requirements
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Any PAL Amiga with 512 Kb of chip memory (you need another 512 Kb of chip
   for the title music).


   Installation
   ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
   Just copy the following files to any directory of your choice:

      Croins
      Croins-TopScores
      Mod.Virtual
      Croins.doc
      Croins.doc.info
      StartCroins
      StartCroins.info (or MWBIcon/StartCroins.info if you have the MagicWB
                        package installed)

   If you delete the Croins-TopScores file, the top scores table will be
   cleared.

   In case you want to create a bootable floppy disk, copy all the files
   from the archive to a disk labelled Croins and install it.


   Usage
   ¯¯¯¯¯
   To run the game open a CLI/Shell window, enter the Croins directory, type
   in 'Croins' and press the Enter key. It can also be started by
   double-clicking the StartCroins icon. You will find more detailed
   instructions within the game.


